OL,3,CCompanies fined after two men crushed
OL,4,Cto death
OL,6,FTwo companies have been fined over the
OL,7,Fdeaths of two workers who were crushed
OL,8,Fwhen an industrial racking system
OL,9,Fcollapsed.
OL,11,FLee Horton, 58, and Daron Pickstock,
OL,12,F43, were killed while testing the
OL,13,Fsystem at Castefields Industrial
OL,14,FEstate in Bingley, West Yorkshire.
OL,16,FThe Health and Safety Executive said
OL,17,Fit was being loaded with test weights
OL,18,Fof up to two tonnes when the structure
OL,19,Fbegan to collapse.
